# Project Structure

## Directory Organization

The web app follows this structure:

```
apps/web/
├── pages/           # Page-specific entry points (HTML + TS)
│   ├── index/
│   ├── search/
│   ├── chat/
│   └── detail/
├── src/
│   ├── components/  # Reusable UI components
│   ├── pages/       # Page initialization logic
│   ├── services/    # API and business logic
│   ├── types/       # TypeScript type definitions
│   ├── utils/       # Utility functions
│   └── styles/      # CSS modules and global styles
├── public/          # Static assets
└── dist/            # Build output (gitignored)
```

## Entry Points

- Main entry: [src/main.ts](mdc:apps/web/src/main.ts) - Routes to page-specific init functions
- Page entries: Each page in `pages/*/index.ts` exports an `init()` function
- Build config: [vite.config.ts](mdc:apps/web/vite.config.ts) defines multi-page build

## Import Paths

- Use relative imports: `../components/AssetCard`
- Import from `src/` when in `pages/` directory: `../../src/services/api`
- Import types: `import type { Asset } from "../types/asset"`
- Import CSS modules: `import styles from "../styles/modules/header.module.css"`

## File Naming

- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `AssetCard.ts`)
- Services/Utils: camelCase (e.g., `api.ts`, `format.ts`)
- Types: camelCase (e.g., `asset.ts`)
- CSS modules: camelCase with `.module.css` suffix

## Page Structure

Each page follows this pattern:
1. HTML file in `pages/{page}/index.html`
2. TypeScript init in `pages/{page}/index.ts` with `export async function init()`
3. Page-specific CSS in `pages/{page}/index.css`
4. Page logic can also be in `src/pages/{page}.ts` for shared code
